b'Jam Pot': b'Described by filmmaker Nobuhiro Kawanaka as \xe2\x80\x98sexier than sex itself\xe2\x80\x99, the film intercuts between close-up images of a naked heterosexual couple and long shots of a bamboo forest taken from above using a helicopter. The edited cut was projected and rephotographed using high contrast black-and-white film, which was printed in 80-100 types of color gradations at the laboratory, creating what looked like a posterization effect.\n\n(Source: Collaborative Cataloging Japan)'
